# Walkthrough: Multi-tenant White-labeling & Agency Identity

I have successfully implemented the white-labeling engine, allowing each agency (tenant) to personalize the entire platform with their own brand identity.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Database & Schema
- Added a `branding` JSON field to the [Tenant](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/lib/tenant-context.ts#12-19) model in Prisma.
- Successfully migrated the database and updated Prisma Client types.

### 2. Global Branding Provider
- Implemented [BrandingProvider](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/components/BrandingProvider.tsx#23-75) in `src/providers/BrandingProvider.tsx`.
- Automatically injects CSS variables (`--primary-brand`, `--sidebar-brand`, etc.) and Google Fonts into the root layout based on the current tenant's settings.

### 3. Responsive Admin Sidebar
- Updated the admin sidebar in [src/app/[locale]/admin/layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/layout.tsx) to dynamically use:
    - **Logo**: Custom image or fallback `Zap` icon.
    - **App Name**: The agency's platform name (e.g., "AgencyX OS").
    - **Sidebar Colors**: Custom background and accent colors.
    - **Fonts**: Dynamic font family loading.

### 4. Self-Service Settings UI
- Created a premium **Identidad Visual** page in the settings section.
- Features:
    - **Live Preview Mockup**: Admins can see changes in a simulated UI before saving.
    - **Color Pickers**: Intuitive selection for primary and sidebar colors.
    - **Font Selection**: Integration with Google Fonts.
    - **Identity Toggle**: Easy switch between custom branding and platform defaults.

## Verification

### Manual Test Steps
1. Navigate to **Settings > Identidad Visual**.
2. Change the **App Name** and **Primary Color**.
3. Observe the **Live Preview** update instantly.
4. Click **Guardar Cambios**.
5. Refresh the page to see the new branding applied to the entire layout and sidebar.

## Technical Details
- **Architecture**: The branding state is resolved server-side in the root layout to prevent "flash of unstyled content" (FOUC).
- **Performance**: Uses standard CSS variables for maximum performance and compatibility with existing Tailwind/Vanilla CSS styles.
